## 3. Background

### 3-1 problems

![61qpiLsM4mL.jpg](https://s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com/secure.notion-static.com/b9b5932a-c95e-4499-9c09-88bac1192335/61qpiLsM4mL.jpg)

```markdown
Since the COVID-19 situation has come to an end, a lot of students have returned to school and the number of vehicles increased accordingly. Therefore, an insufficient parking lot problem aroused. To solve this problem, we came up with the idea to show up parking spaces for the users so that they can park more efficiently.The problem is that there a e not enough parking spaces to accommodate the increase in vehicles, which is causing i convenience for students, faculty, and staff. This problem is impacting the school's operations, as it is creating delays and frustration for those who are unable to find a pa king space, especially in the crowded morning.

```

### 3-2 existing cases, examples, similar studies

```markdown
There are already various services available that provide real-time parking space infor ation. Some well-known examples include "ParkWhiz", "SpotHero", "ParkMobile", and "Park e". These services provide information on available parking spots and allow users to re erve a parking space in their desired location. Companies such as "Park Assist" and "Smart Parking" use cameras within parking lots to detect available parking spaces in real- ime and provide this information to users. In addition to providing real-time parking space information, there are also similar studies being conducted. For example, "ParkNet" is a research project that uses deep learning models for real-time parking space detection. The model detects available parking spaces based on the video input from cameras in the parking lot. "ParkEyes" is another service that combines cameras, IoT sensors, and AI technology to provide real-time information on the location of parked cars and availa le parking spaces within a parking lot. This service helps users easily find their parked car within the parking lot. By referring to similar approaches used in these existing cases, this project can be developed further.
```

### 3-3 objectives

```markdown
The goal of this project is to create a parking service that enables drivers to easily
locate available parking spots in Handong Global University's parking lots. This service aims to reduce the time and effort required for drivers to find a parking spot upon arrival.

```

## 4. Methods

### 4-1 Target user

```markdown
Our target users are Handong students and faculty who use the Handong Smart campus application and drive to school and look for a parking space in the crowded morning. The Handong Smart campus application, which all Handong students use, allows students to access diverse information in Handong. Since every Handong student has access to this applicat on, it will be great for our service to provide parking information through this existing application. Through this application, we can solve the lack of parking lots.

```

### 4-2 technologies

```
AI model : SSD MobileNet (<https://github.com/qfgaohao/pytorch-ssd>)
Input Data : Last image frame from Youtube live stream
Used Library : Youtube-dl, FFMPEG
Databaase : Firebase
Sever : 24 / 7 always activated which run our code unstoppable
Flutter : a frame work which work with dart code and developing ios and android application simultaneously

```

### 4-3 interaction (with sequence diagrams and descriptions)

https://github.com/AnJW-HGU/2023_HCI_Parking/assets/82192969/df3d8071-bd7e-4b02-857f-8aef93d6cc29

```markdown
1. Human Action: Run the Handong Smart Campus application Computer's ACtion: Shows the home screen of the application. The main screen show diverse menus such as “Attendance”, “Major school Notification”, “One click complaints” and our tap, “Parking” section.   
2. Human Action: Press the Parking button on the app Computer's Action: The Handong Campus map screen appears and shows up the availa 											ble parkingspace by each parking lot on the campus. This is done by the machine learning algorithm which classifies the car image on the live video of the parking lot. After it is distinguished, the data is sent
3. Human Action: When the user sets up the notification button, in a specific time period, the app gives notifications.Computer's Action: Based on the user data, the application suggests whether the user drives or not to the school
4. Human Action: Press the number of parking places available on the icon shown on the map Computer's Action: The computer calculates based on the statistical data collected through the users, and provides information about the parking space and which timewill have the higher chances of succeeding parking.
```

### 4-4 Run

1. git clone

`git clone https://github.com/wok1909/HCI_project.git`

1. download git submodules

`git submodule update --init --recursive`

1. Download pytorch-ssd models and pretrained parameters through github page.

link : https://github.com/qfgaohao/pytorch-ssd

1. Run Demo (Using Recorded video)
    1. Prepare a video at `HCI_project/demo`
    2. Run `HCI_project/demo/demo.sh`

1. Run Live (Using Youtube Live Stream)
    1. Prepare a live youtube stream link
    2. Put the link in the shell script code and run
    
    ```c
    #!/bin/bash
    
    rm -f /home/c02002/HCI_project/live/input.jpg
    
    youtube-dl -g -f 95 "YOUTUBE_LIVE_LINK" > ../videos/stream-url
    ffmpeg -i $(cat ../videos/stream-url) -f image2 -frames:v 1 /home/c02002/HCI_project/live/input.jpg
    
    python /home/c02002/HCI_project/pytorch-ssd/run_ssd_db.py \
    			 mb1-ssd \
    			 /home/c02002/HCI_project/pytorch-ssd/models/mobilenet-v1-ssd-Epoch-99-Loss-2.2184619531035423.pth \
    			 /home/c02002/HCI_project/pytorch-ssd/models/open-images-model-labels.txt \
    			 /home/c02002/HCI_project/live/input.jpg \
    			 /home/c02002/HCI_project/live/output.jpg
    ```
    

- Changing the number of total parking lot
    - Change the number of `totalSpace` or you can change the `placeIndex`  in `run_ssd_db.py`

```c
totalSpace = [15, 20, 35, 50]
placeIndex = 0
```

### 6. Conclusion

### 6-1 Limitations

- The proposed solution should also consider the limitations of the school's physical infrastructure, budget constraints, and the time required for implementation.
- On top of that, we need to consider the limitations due to personal data protection laws, such as the protection of vehicle registration numbers.
- By addressing these factors, we aim to propose a solution that will improve the parking situation at the school, enhance the overall experience for students, faculty, and staff, and ensure that the school is accessible and sustainable for all.
1. Budget Constraints: Implementing a parking solution using HCI technology may require financial resources for equipment, software development, maintenance, and infrastructure upgrades. Limited budgetary allocations could pose a constraint on the scale and scope of the project.
2. Technical Feasibility: The successful implementation of the proposed solution relies on the availability and compatibility of camera systems, machine learning algorithms, and the integration of these technologies with the Handong Smart Campus App. Technical challenges, such as system compatibility or limitations in camera coverage, may impact the effectiveness of the solution.
3. Privacy and Data Protection: Collecting and processing data related to parking spaces, such as car detection and occupancy information, raises privacy concerns. Compliance with data protection regulations, particularly regarding the handling of personal information like vehicle registration numbers, must be ensured.
4. User Adoption and Behavior: The success of the solution heavily relies on user adoption and engagement. Encouraging students, faculty, and staff to actively use the app and provide accurate information about parking availability may require incentives, awareness campaigns, and ongoing user support.
5. Campus Infrastructure and Design: The effectiveness of the solution may be influenced by the existing infrastructure and design of the parking lots. Factors such as the number and distribution of parking spaces, accessibility, and potential physical barriers may impact the accuracy of the parking availability information.
6. Maintenance and Upkeep: Ensuring the continued functionality and accuracy of the app requires regular maintenance and updates. Adequate resources and a dedicated team will be necessary to address any technical issues, integrate feedback, and implement improvements over time.
7. Regulatory and Institutional Approval: Obtaining necessary approvals, such as permission to install cameras or make modifications to the SMART CAMPUS APP, from relevant regulatory bodies and institutional stakeholders may be a prerequisite for implementation. Delays or restrictions in obtaining approvals could affect the project timeline.

### 6-2 Future plans

1. Further Develop the Handong Smart Campus App: Continue enhancing the functionality of the app, such as refining the car detection algorithm and improving the accuracy of parking space availability information.
2. Conduct Pilot Testing: Implement a pilot testing phase to gather feedback from a selected group of users, including students, faculty, and staff. This feedback will help identify any areas for improvement and ensure that the app meets the needs of the users.
3. Collaborate with Campus Security and Facilities Management: Work closely with campus security and facilities management teams to integrate the app into their existing systems. This collaboration will help streamline parking management processes and ensure the efficient utilization of parking spaces.
4. Privacy and Data Protection Compliance: Ensure that the app complies with relevant privacy laws and regulations, particularly regarding the protection of personal data such as vehicle registration numbers. Implement robust security measures to safeguard user information.
5. Continuous Improvement and Updates: Regularly update and maintain the app to incorporate user feedback, address any issues or bugs, and introduce new features that enhance the parking experience further. Stay updated with the latest technological advancements in HCI and parking management systems.
6. Collaboration with Local Authorities: Explore opportunities for collaboration with local authorities or municipalities to implement parking solutions at a broader scale. This could involve sharing data and insights to support urban planning and traffic management initiatives.
